	(45,43,'Tell us you\'re coming and we\'ll roll out the pink carpet with reserved parking, kids check-in help, and a friendly host.',1,'2026-03-05 21:29:14',1),
	(46,16,'<ul class=\"info-list\">\n                <li><strong>Services:</strong> Sundays • 11:00AM with live worship &amp; teaching.</li>\n                <li><strong>Kids:</strong> Secure check-in, age-specific teaching, sensory-friendly spaces.</li>\n                <li><strong>Parking:</strong> Look for the pink \"You Belong Here\" flags and our team will guide you.</li>\n                <li><strong>Dress:</strong> Trainers or ties—come as you are.</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Need extra assistance? Email <a href=\"mailto:office@alive.me.uk\">office@alive.me.uk</a> and we\'ll make arrangements.</p>',2,'2026-03-05 21:29:27',1),
	(47,16,'<ul class=\"info-list\">\n                <li><strong>Services:</strong> Sundays • 11:00AM with live worship &amp; teaching.</li>\n                <li><strong>Kids:</strong> Secure check-in, age-specific teaching, sensory-friendly spaces.</li>\n                <li><strong>Parking:</strong> Look for the pink \"You Belong Here\" flags and our team will guide you.</li>\n                <li><strong>Dress:</strong> Trainers or ties—come as you are.</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Need extra assistance? Email <a href=\"mailto:office@alive.me.uk\">office@alive.me.uk</a> and we\'ll make arrangements.</p>',3,'2026-03-05 21:31:11',1),
	(48,19,'jj',1,'2026-03-05 21:32:00',1),
	(49,51,'Kids join us for worship and then go out to their special kids programme just after worship. No need to register. Please rake your child home with you, though.',1,'2026-03-05 21:32:55',1),
	(50,52,'60-75 minutes of worship, teaching, and prayer. Lyrics on screens, seats in back if you prefer. No pressure to participate.',1,'2026-03-05 21:33:09',1),
	(51,52,'60-75 minutes of worship, teaching, and prayer. Lyrics on screens, seats in back if you prefer. No pressure to participate.',2,'2026-03-05 21:33:26',1),
	(52,54,'Stick around for more coffee and conversation in our Revivecafe. Our team can help you find groups, serve opportunities, or next steps.',1,'2026-03-05 21:33:43',1),
	(53,55,'\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>What should I wear?</summary>\n                <p>Come as you are! You\'ll see everything from jeans and trainers to dresses and suits. We care more about you than your outfit.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>Is there parking?</summary>\n                <p>Yes! There is limited parking directly outside the church, and a large free carpark further down Arms Street with plenty of space available. Look for the \"Alive Church Parking\" sign.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>What about my kids?</summary>\n                <p>They can join you, or head up to kids church - either is fine with us!</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>How long is the service?</summary>\n                <p>Plan for 60-75 minutes including worship, teaching, and prayer. You\'re welcome to arrive a few minutes late or leave early if needed. We won\'t condemn you from the stage.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\">\n                <summary>Will I be asked to give money?</summary>\n                <p>We take up an offering for our church family, this is optional for everyone and first time visitors are not under any pressure to give.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\">\n                <summary>Can I bring my service dog?</summary>\n                <p>Absolutely! Service animals are always welcome. Please let us know when you register so we can prepare and assist as needed.</p>\n            </details>        ',1,'2026-03-05 21:35:53',1),
	(54,55,'\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>What should I wear?</summary>\n                <p>Come as you are! You\'ll see everything from jeans and trainers to dresses and suits. We care more about you than your outfit.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>Is there parking?</summary>\n                <p>Yes! There is limited parking directly outside the church, and a large free carpark further down Arms Street with plenty of space available. Look for the \"Alive Church Parking\" sign.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>What about my kids?</summary>\n                <p>They can join you, or head up to kids church - either is fine with us!</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>How long is the service?</summary>\n                <p>Plan for 60-75 minutes including worship, teaching, and prayer. You\'re welcome to arrive a few minutes late or leave early if needed. We won\'t condemn you from the stage.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>Will I be asked to give money?</summary>\n                <p>We take up an offering for our church family, this is optional for everyone and first time visitors are not under any pressure to give. If you do however want to give towards our ministry, there are many easy and accessible ways to do so.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"faq-item\" open=\"\">\n                <summary>Can I bring my service dog?</summary>\n                <p>Absolutely! Service animals are always welcome. Please let us know when you register so we can prepare and assist as needed.</p>\n            </details>        ',2,'2026-03-05 21:36:48',1),
