	(83,9,1,'A look at how everything was made in 7 days','The Bible begins with a powerful and simple truth: God created everything. In this first study, we explore the opening chapter of Genesis and the remarkable account of creation unfolding over six days, with God resting on the seventh. As you read, notice the order, purpose, and intentional design behind everything that was made—from light and land to living creatures and humanity. This passage sets the foundation for understanding God’s power, creativity, and authority over all creation.',NULL,NULL,'Why do you think it was important that on the 7th day, God rested?',NULL),
